3 Jun 2022 20:55:37 +0100</pubDate><guid>/about/</guid><description>&lt;div class="about-grid"&gt;
&lt;div class="about-left"&gt;
&lt;!--&lt;img src="/img/avatar.png" alt="Maciej" class="avatar"&gt;--&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’ve always had a strong curiosity for cybersecurity. Both how attacks happen and how defenders detect them. Over time that curiosity turned into a career working in security operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Early on I spent a lot of time studying offensive techniques used by modern attackers. Understanding how attackers operate, how phishing campaigns are built, how malware spreads, how access is established, made it easier to recognize those same patterns when investigating real alerts. That perspective continues to shape how I approach defensive work today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My day-to-day work focuses on monitoring and investigating security alerts across client environments, analyzing phishing and malware activity, and helping remediate vulnerabilities before they turn into incidents.&lt;/p&gt;
